name: ALL ALLIES ALL LIES
description: Can anyone really know someone else? Deep down we are these need/want creatures that lie on a daily basis. But why? Why do we lie so much? They could be the smallest of lies or the biggest; we're programmed to lie for self preservation. We ally ourselves with other like minded people who also lie and ally themselves with other people like them who lie...and the cycle repeats itself all over the globe. What is it about human nature that makes us lie? Most of us don't intentionally lie to be hurtful to others. Is it part of our reptilian brain that causes us to fib to preserve our ego or to preserve our life? Big distinction there. Things to think about.
